reviews.text: Wish I came earlier, it looks like a fun place to hang out and visit shops. Everything was pretty much closed when I arrived around 7pm. Maybe next time. Still got to see the Bruce Lee monument and take great pictures!

Gracious shop owners, fair restaurants, open spaces. 
However, this space has many shop closures, so it isn't as bustling a space as, say, Little Tokyo or the Chinatown of old. 
Most likely, it won't be what you expected, and you will struggle to spend an entire afternoon in the area. 
Overall, it's good, but not great, and by no means is it a current Los Angeles must-see.

A nice tourist destination and a cool place to buy souvenirs. I’d hoped to see a bit more food choices but it was still a good experience. I’m not sure this is necessarily one of the things that you “must” do if you are in LA but if you are already close by, it wouldn’t be bad to walk through and check it out.

I'm sure this used to be more populated and better than what it is now. Mostly the elderly people around. Apparently this was where Rush Hour was filmed. There's a Bruce Lee statue there. Definitely nothing compared to NYC Chinatown. Barely any Asian supermarkets or street vendors. They need to fix this place up and bring back the younger Cantonese group back to make it feel more like Chinatown.

One of my favorite areas in Los Angeles, great architecture, great food and local merchants are always happy to see new faces and help customers. Went there for Lunar Year parade and it was awesome. I recommend taking the subway, Red Line than Gold Line to avoid traffic and parking issues. Really fun for family and gives people a taste of LA's thriving urban scene.

I have been eating here since I was a kid (I'm 35). The deep-fried spring rolls are to die for. The owner and family are wonderful. Don't be fooled by the simple decor - the food is wonderful and from a first-generation Vietnamese Canadian who knows good food with classic techniques. Thanks for 25 years of fantastic dining!!!
The food: Fantastic. The service: Speedy and friendly. The portions: Huge. The price: Great. The wonderful free tea: The finishing touch to a perfect meal. Eat here. Full stop.
Food was great and cheap! They serve some nice tea as well with your meal. The staff was really friendly 😊!
I love his place! The food is always hot and fresh, the service friendly and the prices are more than reasonable. Would highly recommend!

Good service but very dirty restaurant and the most bland and basic pad Thai I've ever eaten, and I've eaten a lot of pad Thai!! I'd suggest eating elsewhere for both a cleaner environment and more flavour. There are lots of good Thai and Vietnamese restaurants in London. Thaifoon and Tamarine on Dundas are both amazing. Thai Cuisine on Gainsborough too.

Stopped here for a quick coffee and was impressed by the service, cleanliness and quality. Ordered a Piccolo latte using local beans from Chiang Rai and it was perfect. We could pay with card which was a bonus and the restaurant was nice and air conditioned. Best coffee experience in the city.

Price : relatively high in CM but reasonable.
Location : Near the eastern gate of the city. Easy to reach.
Food : Nice both of the taste and the outlook
Environment :nice I think it should be a nice place for dating.

OMG!  I'm totally in love with this place, not only the decoration, staff are nice with friendly smile always,  delicious food, reasonable price.  They have a nice shop here too.
You MUST come when you at Chiang Mai, highly recommend! 😍😍😍😍😍
Very nice dishes and service. The atmosphere was very nice as well.

Not as good as I had hoped, the staff and service was fantastic. But for what was my most expensive meal our so far in Thailand I was left quite underwhelmed, Tom Yum soup had no spice or body to it, the only good point where the three large prawns in there.

The Stinking Rose has been in LA longer than I can remember.  I went when I was much younger and then again not too long ago while on vacation in LA.  It was as good as I remember and would love to go again.

Firstly, you can't help but be impressed with the decor.  It's like eating in your own private cabana somewhere in an exotic location.  It's unlike any other interior I've seen.  Then, while you wait for your food, they bring out the most incredible warm garlic rolls which are just heavenly.  So yum.  There's plenty on the menu to choose from, and everything sounds delicious.  I had a beautiful pasta dish, and wasn't disappointed.  The food came out promptly and the staff were friendly and nice.

I DO hate how some restaurants provide valet parking (because there's sometimes just not other choice) and then charge the earth.  But luckily we got a park right outside.

If you're a garlic fan, and love comfort dishes set in a beautiful restaurant with a great ambiance and in a central location in LA, then try the Stinking Rose.  It's well priced and a great experience.

Customer services:5/5
Quality of food: 3/5
Price: 20-50/per

This place is like a theme park! Interior is so cute and fun. Price is good in area and there are vegetarian options as well. But quality of food is depends on what you order. Stake was good but pork-chop was little dry and hard.

Iconic place with fantastic food. A classic Los Angeles staple with a delicious theme 👌👌. It's a beautiful spot with lots of neat decor. Beware, you will leave smelling like Garlic, yes or yes, but it'll be worth it for the delicious experience. Lots of fun and worth the price.

My hubby and I had an excellent time here! I love the little Cabanas they're so private and you feel like you have your own little luxurious restaurant to yourself it's amazing the service is wonderful the food is delicious and the garlic ice cream is a must-try it's interesting and different but if you've never tried it you have to do it just for the experience!

Went for out anniversaries and as being garlic lovers this was definitely a choice for us. Food was great but prices were eve n better. For being in Beverly hills and the amount of talk that goes on with this place it was definitely priced right. We got 2 appetizers, our entree, unlimited bread, pesto and was even able to bring your own bottle of wine - with no cork fee. Total cane out to $99 on the point. Deliciousness and service all in one!

Everything is so fresh and light. Definitely does not leave you feeling overly stuffed. The nacho chips are all freshly made along with the black bean chili and.. well everything else on the menu here! The cauliflower buffalo "wings" are a great appetizer and you have to try the vegan chili. You can't believe it's vegan!
Great craft cocktails, delicious scratch-made desserts. The hard-core meat eater in our group loved his vegetarian nachos! Plenty of vegan options.
Great service, excellent selection of Sunday brunch items. Gluten free options are marvelous! Thanks for caring about us.
Best food better staff.  I love this place so much I have to refrain from eating it everyday.  10/10 would go into a food coma again.
Great food. Good drinks. Friendly service. Neat spot

This is my favorite restaurant in Dayton area.  I've been going here for around 20 years.  I would highly recommend one of the meal sized soups, like saté style (#37) and the soft shrimp roll (#2) is amazing. Everyone I've brought for the 1st time always loves these, and the peanut sauce they come with is a mind expanding experience.  The crispy egg noodles (#61) are also a favorite. The fried bananas are a perfect dessert (#184). I have also never been disappointed when trying new dishes of the menu

I don't know where to start when it comes to Little Saigon. Their food is AMAZING! Sincerely, it is so good and flavorful with so many options I know I will never try them all. I maintain they have the best friend spring rolls in the area. They have such delicious Vietnamese dishes with such a huge selection you just have to see their menu to understand. The staff there is so sweet and nice and try so hard to make sure you enjoy your experience. I also think the prices are reasonable, especially with the portions you receive.
Food is great! A good place to get rice when I'm craving for it. Lol. Try their crab rangoon.  It's the best. I also love their fresh spring rolls. 😊

This adorable little Resturaunt was pleasant, and the staff were fun and easy to talk to. Not to mention the food was AMAZING. It was incredible flavorful and there we so many options! Overall, a very VERY good place to eat of your looking to try something new and filling!

This place is a gem! The staff is great, the variety and selection of dishes are extensive and the food itself is amazing. If you enjoy vietnamese food or Asian food in general, this is one of the truly authentic Asian restaurants in the Dayton area. You will not be dissapointed!

Delicious food and excellent service! Tonight was our first experience eating Indian cuisine. Our waiter was knowledgeable and friendly with his recommendations and my husband and I both truly enjoyed our experiences.  We would recommend this restaurant to friends and family, and we will definitely be coming back ourselves.
This place was great. We ordered Lamb chops and chicken masala? (The first menu in curry categories) and they were nice. We will visit there again definitely.
The food is amazing and the wait staff so friendly. Every time we are in Ann Arbor we eat there as no other Indian restaurant is as good. We've been eating there for 20 years.

One of the best Indian restaurants I've eaten at and I have been eating there for years. Reminds me of the nicer Indian restaurants in Great Brittan where I first tried Indian food. Authentic food served in a very nice atmosphere. The waiters are all very professional and efficient. I asked about a dish I used to order but was not on the menu now and the waiter said they would make it for me... Chicken Hyderabadi (not sure I spelled that right) delicious! I'll back when I'm in town again.

The food is delicious in every word possible! I went with my mom, and she's usually picky when it comes to food, but she absolutely loved their food. Our waiter was the best! The prices are not that bad. The service was good, a man in a suit (I believe the owner) came to our to check up on us. All in all, it was a great first experience.

Awesome castle to visit.  One of the best I have been to.  The castle offers commanding views of the city of Edinburgh.  Lots of great exhibits to what life was once like in the castle.  The also have exhibits discussing the various branches of the armed forces, their exploits and sacrifices.  There is a dog cemetery for regimental dogs.  If you want a deeper dive into the history you can higher a guide, use a tour, or purchase the audio tour add on.  They are not necessary but for history buffs they will be well worth it.  If you were selecting one of these options be prepared to spend at least 2-3 hours at the castle.  Even without them you can easily spend an hour and that is rushing through and not having to stand in line.  Do yourself a favor and purchase your tickets ahead of time.  Otherwise you may have a long wait.  Also dress appropriately.  It is cold and windy on top of Castle Rock.

Amazing Castle overlooking the entire city of Edinburgh. You can actually see the old town and new town divide from the castle. Castle is very impressive with lots of history to learn. There are lots of little areas inside the castle to see, I won't ruin them for you :). The surrounding ding shopping and dining is also very good. This castle is a must see if you are visiting Edinburgh for the first time.

Edinburgh Castle was truly incredible and a must see while in Edinburgh. It’s exactly what you think of when you think of grand medieval castles and you could easily spend hours exploring all the grounds and history here. Plus the views from the top of the castle are great and you can walk around the entirety of the walls which was awesome.

If you are in Edinburgh you have to visit the castle. You can definitely see the amount of attention to details and how well maintained everything is. The place is very rich with history and stories. Consider spending a couple of hours here and definitely go for buying your tickets online to avoid spending a lot of time in the lines. Enjoyed the visit and as well the view you get with the city.

A must see if in Edinburgh.   Just the view alone was fantastic. Pictures do not do it justice.  It is well preserved and you have many places to explore on the grounds.  We did the audio tour and liked it but I think the guided tour would have been more fun but we did not have the time.  We got our tickets to the Castle from the Edinburgh Hop-On-Hop-Off Tour we purchased which saved us some money.

Love walking into a Starbucks and smelling the fresh coffee. This location was clean and the staff friendly. Coffee was made to order and correctly made for this picky coffee drinker lol. This spot has an area for when you are wanting to socialize or break out the computer/books and do some studying while sipping on a latte. Only problem I seen was the drive through and parking area are very tight but couldn't take a star away just for that. Keep it up at this location cause my little girl and I will definitely be back for our coffee.
Always fast, friendly, and informative! Their coffee is great and their snacks are always yummy! Mobile pickup through their app is always very convenient as well!

Yummy but prices need to stop going up, they  are beyond being a very successful business that has millions of people addicted and stopping for ine of their many yummy beverages and foods almost every day like its crack, stop being greedy with the cost increase of everything, PLEASE. I want to be able to afford my coffee "crack" lol just playing, kinda. Attention there's no illegal drugs served at any Starbucks facility
... that I'm aware of!
Very friendly service. Got the order correct. Fast.
Rude, impersonal staff, slow service, dirty restrooms. The food is blah, you get better quality food at much lower prices at McDonalds or any of the other fast food chains in the area.
This museum gave a very brief overview of the maritime industry in Croatia. If visiting, I suggest purchasing the Dubrovnik card which will allow entry to this and other museums.
An interesting range of exhibits and the museum is worth a visit if you have a few days in Dubrovnik.

This is a nice place to visit if you're on the Dubrovnik Card.
Lots of nice exhibits, takes you back in time though the perspective of the most important trade in Dubrovnik's history.

Worth checking out if you've purchased the Dubrovnik pass, otherwise quite expensive. Lots of interesting maritime history directly related to the area. You're not permitted to take pictures (why?) I still took a couple.. Ssshhhhh ;)
Great presentation in very fitting environment

This was my first time I had eaten at in and Out Burger. I absolutely loved it however I'm trying to eat better and every time I drive by one of these I have to stop now. So there goes my eating better right out the window. Happy face covered in ketchup. The staff was great in fact they were really funny which was fun in the food of course it's in and out burger is great

Our favorite place to eat! The fries are the best! The employees are always friendly. The burgers are by far the best in all of California. I come here way too often. Its conveniently located close to school so I don’t have to travel a long ways!

Was disappointed with my visit to in-n-out tonight. Food was cold and the taste wasn't up to standards. The staff were incredible and they all greeted me with a smile but, the food was off. I do have to say the Milk shake was delicious. However, both the double double and the fries were served cold and the burger was under cooked. Never received an under cooked burger from In-n-out, so I am sure my next visit will be better hopefully.

What can I say?  In n Out is always great.  The line was out the door for eat in, and out the driveway and into the street for drive through.  It was 2:30 pm on Saturday.  I had a complicated order, which they got right.  The 40-minute wait made me grumpy, that's why just four stars.
Friendly people, delicious food and for the most part fast. If it was not such a long line I would've given it 5 stars! I will be coming back here if I'm in the area

This is our main store for shopping close to home! It can be pretty spendy at times with prices, but with Just4U coupons help a lot!! They have some great deals at times. If you want quality and a variety even with Safeway brands  Safeway is great for that. They have a deli, bakery and pharmacy. They also have a Starbucks inside. The one complaint I have lately with them is their meat department. The quality of their meat isn't as great as it use to be. We've found bone grit on the pork and bones in boneless skinless chicken. Otherwise I love their produce, breads, desserts and products!! Plus you'll always get GREAT customer service and asked if you need help out!! Or you can also do self checkout instead.

All and all it's not a bad place to shop... it's a little spendy... you definitely need to watch for deals... The cashiers are pretty nice..The pharmacy and their employees are Rock Stars... Trevor is one of the pharmacist who always goes above and beyond to take care of your needs... Thank you ever so much Trevor... yes, Amy your pretty awesome... Thank you kindly... :-) :-) :-)

This store is brightly lit and well maintained. We usually go to Costco for a lot of reasons but for small and unique grocery purchases we end up at Safeway. The checkers at this location are almost always pleasant and attentive, both things that aren't always guaranteed these days.
Its a grocery store chain. The quality is good. The price is a little high, but they offer a membership discount.

The old lady in the deli is absolutely the rudest person I’ve ever met in my life she constantly makes you feel like your bothering her that you want a sandwhich rolled her eyes and got huffy puffy that I asked for bacon and proceeded to say “I guess, but that’s gonna cost more” (like I didn’t already know that) then didn’t ask me if I wanted anything else threw my snadwhich on the counter and walked away. I will never be going back there again so disappointed

These cats are the bomb!  I've run a number of Chinese visa requests through them and every transaction has been timely and flawless.  If you need visa services from one of the Chicago consulates, this the place to go!

I love vegetarian and vegan food, and there are some great options in the East Bay, but this place is mediocre at best. I'm always astounded to see that it's filled with people, because each time I've eaten here I've found that the food lacks flavor. Instead of having a huge selection with sub-par food, they should probably focus on serving a smaller number of dishes that actually taste good.
I love coming here.  It's not perfect, but I always come away very satisfied.  Love the great selection, and service is always friendly.

Food is good.  The shakes are awesome!  The service can be slow.  Other than that, it's worth giving it a try especially if you are a vegetarian or vegan.  Even if you are not, the flavors are good enough that you won't miss the meat.

The food is hearty vegan fare.  I had their homemade ginger ale which was delightful.  For a main dish their lasagna which also came with salad.
The dressing was tasty yet the salad a bit over-dressed and slightly wilted like it sat by the hot food a bit too long.
The lasagna was delish, filling, hearty if a tad saltier than I'm used to.  
All in all, good hearty solid cooked fare.
Great service! Friendly spot to meet up with friends - we hung out there for almost 4 hours and they were so flexible and hospitable with us.

O man, I am too old for this place but anyone under 25 would love this spot.  Great spot for singles to meet others.  It's like a dive bar nightclub.  Cash only thing is weird but I assume they just don't want to run 200 tabs at once since this place gets super busy.  I would recommend this spot for any younger kids.

Stopped here after being recommended this spot from a friend.  

This place was very busy, popular, and full on a Tuesday.  That was quite surprising to me.  I believe they have music every night, which is a huge plus.  I can see this spot being very ideal for a lot of folks, but for a particular demographic.

There were a few things I just couldn't get over.  The volume level of the band was absolutely ATROCIOUS.  It was SO loud, we couldn't even hear ourselves talk and we were outside, away from the speakers.  The levels were off and far too loud.  Anyone inside was clearly damaging their hearing.  This level of volume was so uncomfortable we were forced to leave and go elsewhere.    Mind you I work music festivals and large events for a living, so for the volume to be loud for me, this was quite a feat.

Also, cash only.

Place has history, great bartenders, awesome music and great beach views. Bring cash. No card. Has been iconic for over 80 years. This is a place you cant afford to miss out on when u visit laudy beach.
Good music and food, friendly environment. The staff was very professional and proficient. Live band downstairs and TVs, drinks and chill out upstairs.
A really cool dive bar across street from Ocean. Great views and good music.  Bartenders are attentive and quick to serve. A must stop when in Fort Lauderdale. Great for people watching.

reviews.author_name: Alpha omega King The Realist G
reviews.text: Great crew staff will point u in the right direction.

Very cool place, kind of in an odd place, you have to go in a building and walk to it. Other than that no complaints. Nice view from within the city, priced pretty well for the quality of food. We went for my birthday and they gave us a free desert so huge shout out to them! Highly recommend for nice nights out for an anniversary, birthday, or to just have a nice sit down dinner!

Excellent restaurant. The service is really good. The location is great, it overlooks fountain square. We’ve had pizza, pasta and many of the appetizers and they are all amazing. I recommend the bruschetta and the fried cheese.

Still one of my favorite restaurants, although its lost some of its luster.  It's showing its age a bit.  Service doesn't quite have the intangible extra it once had.  The food is still good and it still has the spectacular view of Fountain Square.  Overall, very good, but not great.

We organised our corporate dinners here, so was our this one. Food was great & our colleagues have been taken care well. Ambiance was nice because we were larger group so they did provide us private room. They were only people who acknowledge our booking on Saturday for dinner placed on Monday. I give only 1 star less, just because my usual experience is time they take to serve food it can go up to an hour, so plan your time accordingly. While this might be just because they were trying to maintain quality or one of cook is on long weekend ;-)

Every time I go downtown to meet my investment team they always take me to palominos. They know it's my all-time favorite for lunch. Overlooks Fountain Square Downtown , perfect spot for lunch and dinner.

Great venue for small, private events. Staff are professional and accommodating. Presentation of food looked appealing and but the taste was not as good. Drink selections for the event was limited, only still water, wine and carbonated juice were available.

Personally, I think the level of the restaurant was average for both food and service at the time of my visit. My wife and I came with a tour group. It was obvious that we are treated differently compared with other customers who made the reservations themselves. Although the staff were polite, the dishes were served without proper introductions. As for the food, it was not bad but below my expectation.

Elegant place. If you want to find a place to relax and taste some liquor, take a chance on this. Surprisingly, I came at Sat night, but only a few customers. The price is reasonable, for my long island is 175.000 vnd.
Nice place, nice food
Nice restaurant with good service but not so high European level. Price is affordable. I will recommend it

A bar that offers happy hour in Fes, Morocco?  We had to check it out.

Great views of the garden on the terrace.  The cushions are a bit dirty and torn up but eh.  The service was slow but once it started to fill up, our server was around more.

The happy hour is kind of a joke.  Order 2 beers, get the 3rd free but only per person and they give you all 3 at the same time.

We enjoyed our evening of drinks and the best Hookah we’ve had so far in Morocco. This is the only ‘bar’ we found in the area.  Staff were really friendly and the wine was nice and cold. Shame we ran out of time and couldn’t make it back another night.
Nice location, more potential, alcohol available ;)

seems to be one of the few places to have a drink in Fes !  the prices are a little high but considering the alcohol shortage,  you cant complain.  They also have local Moroccan beer which is pretty good.
One of very little places you get an actual alcoholic drink and mine long island for 80dh was pretty juicy - read strong. Nice terrace on top, really cozy place.

Beautiful rose garden, well maintained. Do come on weekends. Its located in sector 15. Space for car parking also available. You can enjoy coconut water, various flavor of ice creams, lemon soda. Best time to visit is in evening as it glows various colour full lights there. Lot of fountains with ample sitting space. Best for jogging yoga exercise, whatever you love to do.

The Rose Garden as the name suggest has different varieties of roses white , red, Yellow, orange,pink with a specific scientific name written...
The sizes of roses are also very Big.
The park is large and spread over 30 acres..
The garden is well maintained with good grass..
The trees also beautiful..
It also has a fountain..

Good to spend time here
Moreover eating facilities and washrooms are also available..
A Nala passes in between the park and has bridge to cross over it..

My mom used to come here when she lived in Chandigarh for a while. When I visited, it was nice. However, i noticed that the water (lake) was drained. It did not look very aesthetic. Wish they were fixing it at a different time. The flowers look very beautiful. If you are in Chandigarh, I recommend visiting this garden. It is also a great place for studying or reading (or relaxing in general). I just want to put out a request for people to not damage the flowers and plants. If you are taking photos, please be aware of your surroundings. This is a beautiful place, and we should keep it this way.

Visited during summer vacations and hardly found any rose. Summer definitely not the right time to visit the garden. There is not much greenery also to sit during summer. Recommended for other seasons. Kids did not enjoy much and all we could see was little squirrel 🐿 at entrance. Must be much better place during season other than summer.

Opened in 1967, this place has been one of the scenic beauty types place where you can visit anytime for nice views. The garden is well managed by the managing body. Also if you are one who is very fond of roses and would like to take a look at different varieties of roses, then this is the place for you. Also during the time of valentine's week, there is a rose festival organised here. So visit this place during this time and you will definitely worth it. For the rest of the year, this place is chic and quiet. So a good place for finding peaceful environment for a short time in a day or so

Pad See Ew (Medium Spicy, Beef) was phenomenal. The noodles were pretty excellent in texture and taste, the egg/beef/broccolli were cooked just the right amount, and the sauce and spices were fantastic. Medium spice level is not for the faint of heart, so try the lowest level spice first if you don't know what you are getting into. The wait staff is erratic but that wasn't enough to deter from the quality and flavor of the dish!
One of the better Thai spots in the area. Can actually deliver on spiciness if requested. Friendly and quick service, decent parking options nearby.
My first time here. I had the Panang (mild) it was absolutely delicious!! Had chicken satay for appetizer, also very very good. I recommend to all Thai Food lovers

Food was okay. Not the greatest, not the worst. The worst thing about the experience was the decore and the chairs. They were really uncomfortable to sit in and reminded me of the set my grandmother has in her dining room. The decore doesnt match the atmosphere of the restaurant. If i do ever come back, its to order take out.
I ordered the hottest on their menu, result=not hot in the least bit, added my own cayenne pepper, won't order from here again

Great selection of shops, places for food and the cinema. Toilets in good condition, including family rooms for those with more demanding needs. Train station on the one side, bus station on the other. Comfortable 10 min stroll into the centre of Aberdeen.

Just a shopping mall with loads of chain stores. There is nothing distinctive about this place to make it particularly pertinent to Aberdeen.
That is not to say the shops or restaurants are poor quality. It's just that they could be anywhere in the UK.

Good clean shopping mall, good shops and restaurants. Enjoyed the cinema and the popcorn. The fact that you can bring a beer into the cinema is really good! The mall is clean and well maintained with stalls on Saturday that makes it a bit different. The bus and train station are there too which makes it comfortable
The shops are good, but there simply aren't enough of them. Union Square should have another level. 3 rather than 2 would've provided enough shops to cater for all.

It's a great place to go if you like to queue. You queue to get in. You queue to park your car. You queue to pay in the shops. You queue to get something to eat. You queue to pay for the pleasure of queuing. Then guess what when you want to leave, you have to queue.

Closer to 4.5

This American-Mexican restaurant is a slightly-hidden gem with some standout menu offerings. Located in a strip mall sandwiched between a Dollar Store and an insurance company, one might be quick to dismiss this...but that would be a mistake. 

The restaurant itself is immaculately clean. Decor is bright and cheerful. Seating is a mix of booths and tables. I have had service ranging from disinterested to, literally, the best server experience in Corvallis.

Menu items are typical, but taste fresh and some nice attention to detail. May I recommend the Diabla burrito...a very spicy mixture of meat (I prefer shrimp), vegetables, and rice in a secret red sauce that is fire! Topped with sour cream and guacamole it is my favorite dish that never disappoints. 

The margaritas are strong and cold and the free chips come with salsa and beans.

This is a must!  Absolutely awesome service!  You're more like family than a customer!  The inside looks fantastic as well! 
Have you seen the bar in the back?! Phenomenal atmosphere if you're looking for a lighter ambience.
The food matches everything else!
Great prices for lunch. Pretty standard fair food but the place is clean and our waiter was attentive. Food was ready super quick. Definitely be back.

Pretty good for Mexican American food. I mean, it's not quite like dining in old Mexico, but that's a much longer drive. If you've never had it, you could order a plate with enchiladas. It comes with rice and beans. Or some grilled chicken. It also comes with rice and beans. But you get the point.
Pretty generic Mexican restaurant. Had enchiladas rancheras and it was good.

Beautiful location but service makes Parisien waiter look good.....
When the serving staff at the central bar deem to acknowledge your existence (10 minutes in my case with a half full bar) the presentation is spot on.
Perhaps if the service wasn't included the staff would try harder and probably get bigger tips too!!
Lovely Grand Cafe setting. Very upmarket shops too. An overall fantastic experience!

Nice place with some high-end, though not exclusive shopping and dining. Especially good if you have more money than sense or just want to show off a little. Bit of a tourist trap in some sense, but food and drinks are decent.
Historic building next to the Bank of England. High End shopping with excellent dining.
This is a great venue in the City.  A Fortnum and Masons Art Deco bar, was not was I was expecting! I only stopped for a post work tipple , but will be sure to sample the menu on my next visit.
Awesome burritos!
